{"title_page": "Mei (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 Tamil-language crime thriller film}}\n{{Use Indian English|date = September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Mei\n| image          = Mei poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = S. A. Bhaskaran\n| producer       = \n| writer         = S. A. Bhaskaran\n| story          = Sentha Murugesan\n| starring       = Nicky Sundaram<br />[[Aishwarya Rajesh]]<br />[[Kishore (actor)|Kishore]]\n| music          = Anil Prithvi Kumar\n| cinematography = VN Mohan\n| Editor         = Preethi Mohan\n| studio         = Sundaram Productions\n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|df=y|2019|08|23}}\n| runtime        = 130 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| based on       = \n| Film Editor    = Preethi Mohan\n}}\n\n'''''Mei''''' ({{trans|Truth/ Body}}) is a 2019 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[medical fiction|medical]] [[thriller film]] written and directed by S. A. Bhaskaran in his directorial debut. The film stars newcomer Nicky Sundaram, [[Aishwarya Rajesh]], [[Kishore (actor)|Kishore]] and [[Charle]] in the lead roles. The film is based on the real story relating to medical mafias in India.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sify.com/movies/aishwarya-rajesh-mei-will-expose-the-irregularities-in-the-medical-field-news-tamil-tiuljLbbhgice.html|title=Aishwarya Rajesh: 'Mei' will expose the irregularities in the medical field|work=Sify|access-date=24 September 2019|language=en}}</ref> The film is produced under the production banner Sundaram Productions. The music for the film is composed by debutant Anil Prithvi Kumar and the editing was done by preethi mohan, cinematography is handled by VN Mohan. The film was released on 23 August 2019 and received good reviews from the audience and critics.<ref name=ie>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/review/2019/aug/24/mei-review-this-medical-thriller-saves-no-one-2023483.html|title='Mei' review: This medical thriller saves no one|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=24 September 2019}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.sify.com/movies/mei-review-a-watchable-crime-thriller-review-tamil-tixuCOfefbhbc.html|title=Review : Mei review: A watchable crime thriller (2019)|website=www.sify.com|access-date=2019-09-24}}</ref><ref name=hi>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/mei-movie-review-a-topical-subject-watered-down-by-lacklustre-filmmaking/article29234522.ece|title=Mei\u2019 movie review: A topical subject watered down by lacklustre filmmaking|last=S|first=Srivatsan|date=2019-08-23|work=The Hindu|access-date=24 September 2019|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nThe missing case of a young girl unfolds mystery behind several hidden crimes related to a medical racket as investigation continues.<ref name=toi>{{Citation|title=Mei Movie Review {2.5/5}: Critic Review of Mei by Times of India|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movie-reviews/mei/movie-review/70801183.cms|access-date=24 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nAbhinav Chandran (Nicky Sundaram), an aspiring doctor who returned from US, is chased by police when medical racket alleges him for the reason behind the death of a medical shop employee. He is assisted by medical representative Uthra (Aishwarya Rajesh).<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== Cast ==\n* Nicky Sundaram as Dr. Abhinav Chandran\n* [[Aishwarya Rajesh]] as Uthra\n* [[Kishore (actor)|Kishore]] as Muthu\n* [[Charle]]\n* Ajay Ghosh\n* Vinod Krishnan\n* [[Kavithalaya Krishnan]]\n\n==Soundtrack==\nSoundtrack was composed by debutant Prithvi Kumar.<ref>https://www.raaga.com/tamil/movie/mei-songs-T0004796</ref>\n*Maalaiye - Prithvikumar\n*Kaatre Silamurai - Pradeep Kumar\n*Maayavalai - Prithvikumar, Sanjana Raja\n\n== Marketing ==\nThe official trailer of the film was unveiled on 15 August 2019, coinciding the [[Independence Day of India]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/videos/entertainment/regional/tamil/mei-official-trailer/videoshow/70698158.cms|title=Mei&nbsp;\u2013 Official Trailer {{!}} Tamil Movie News&nbsp;\u2013 Times of India|website=timesofindia.indiatimes.com|access-date=24 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n''The Hindu'' wrote \"As the title suggests, Mei is about finding the truth behind The Curious Case of A Missing Girl. But it\u2019s a weakly-scripted movie that doesn\u2019t quite take off.\"<ref name=hi /> ''Times of India'' wrote \"The story and characters look too good on paper with some twists and a few engaging sequences. [..] However, the making of a slick thriller like this could have been more gripping as it lacks any sharp cuts or edge of the seat moments\".<ref name=toi /> ''The New Indian Express'' wrote \"One of the oft-used conclusions drawn about a middling movie is that it has its heart in the right place. Unfortunately, for Mei, a film based on organ trafficking, I can\u2019t quite say that\".<ref name=ie /> ''Sify'' wrote \"Overall,  \u2018Mei\u2019 is a watchable thriller for the research work done by the young team, the strong supporting cast and the crisp run time\".<ref name=\":0\" />\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n== External links ==\n\n* {{IMDb title|id=tt10814494}}\n{{2010s-Tamil-film-stub}}\n[[Category:2019 directorial debut films]]\n[[Category:Indian crime thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s crime thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films based on actual events]]\n[[Category:Films about organ trafficking]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 Tamil-language crime thriller film}}\n{{Use Indian English|date = September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Mei\n| image          = Mei poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = S. A. Bhaskaran\n| producer       = \n| writer         = S. A. Bhaskaran\n| story          = S